6:
I hereby declare my intention to
expand my business into another
world.
17:
Like Palpebra, Qualia City celebrates
the holiday, though the origins of it
are lost to us.
19:
Businesses have utilized the holiday
for profit in many ways. I believe I
can do the same.
22:
Huh... Well, it's not a bad idea. You're
aiming to expand into Palpebra,
then?
25:
That is the plan. However, I need to
learn more about local customs, in
order to avoid offending anyone.
31:
Would you like to attend Palpebra's
celebration with me?
45:
No. As this is part of my own training
for personal growth, she doesn't
need to be here!
47:
Besides, I've already made
arrangements with others...
58:
The holiday is a combination of
local beliefs, capitalism, and
entertainment for the children...
*munch*
66:
It's crucial to take things in from the
consumer's point of view!
71:
Hahaha, it's good to see you
enjoying the festivities. Your outfit
looks great, by the way!
75: Yes, it's very cool and cute.
80:
Isn't it? I was right to ask Falsche for
her knowledge on Palpebra's
Halloween.
84:
...Are you sure you want to be
dressed as a reaper though?
89:
Why not? I quite like the big scythe
and the black clothes.
95:
Which is why I enjoy your usual outfit
as well, though the one you have on
now is nice in its own way.
99: ...Thank you, Love. You look great too.
103:
Besides, reapers are in the same
category as ghosts, aren't they?
106:
Anyone with sense would know
better than to fear something
imaginary.
120:
If you're trying to scare me, it won't
work.
122:
I realize you and Lich might believe
in ghosts.
124:
But that is because you both
possess special powers. There's no
proof that they exist for the rest of us—
128:
Love... Sorry to break it to you, but
ghosts really do exist.
133:
Noooope! You're lying, I know you
are!
136:
I won't fall for your tricks! There's
always a perfectly rational
explanation for the supernatural!
146: Ah! Love, don't look behind you...
161:
J-just kidding! H-haha, how's that
for a Halloween prank?
174:
Don't worry. I made sure to tone it
down so it only stings a little!
188:
There was actually one more reason
why I decided on this outfit.
191:
I admit, I was jealous of the girl who
was able to hear the voices of the
lost.
193:
I can't even manage a proper
conversation with those still alive...
196:
Are you talking about that
Conductor guy and Radius?
Whatever happened with them?
199: Nothing. I simply... let things be.
205:
All you need to do is give the
command, and we'll handle the rest.
209:
Go wherever you like, Love. Should
you require our assistance, you
know where to find us.
211:
After all, resources like us are made
to be used.
215:
...Quite demanding for someone
asking for orders, aren't you?
221:
Truthfully, I no longer had the right
to command them, and yet I
allowed myself to indulge in their
kindness.
229:
You managed to speak with Bulleta,
remember?
233:
It's not like you'll never have the
chance to either. Pretty sure the
Conductor wouldn't mind if you
dropped in sometime.
238:
...It sounds so simple when you put it
that way.
240: You have a point. One day—
244:
One day soon. Tomorrow is never
guaranteed, as I have learned.
247:
I'll speak my honest feelings, just like
Bulleta can.
250:
But before then, I should prepare
some souvenirs to bring back.
253: I trust you won't mind helping?
